# Movie Browser Project

## Overview
- **Tech Stack**: Nuxt.js 3, Vue.js, TMDB API, MongoDB, Vuetify
- **Purpose**: Movie and TV series discovery platform with user authentication and ratings
- **Live Site**: themoviebrowser.com

## SEO Optimizations Completed

### Core SSR & Hydration Fixes
- ✅ Enabled SSR (`ssr: true`) in nuxt.config.ts
- ✅ Fixed `ClientOnly` components causing hydration mismatches
- ✅ Modified `IntersectionLoader` to render content during SSR
- ✅ Enhanced data fetching with proper `useLazyAsyncData` configurations
- ✅ Added canonical tags to all key pages

### Content & Structure
- ✅ Implemented HTML5 semantic tags (`<article>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<main>`)
- ✅ Enhanced image alt attributes for better accessibility and image SEO
- ✅ Added Schema.org microdata for Movie/TVSeries structured data
- ✅ Optimized global meta tags and Open Graph data

### Performance & Core Web Vitals
- ✅ Configured image optimization (WebP/AVIF, quality: 80, densities: [1,2])
- ✅ Added preconnect/dns-prefetch for external resources
- ✅ Enabled asset compression and minification
- ✅ Implemented header-based caching (`s-maxage`) for better performance

### Automated Sitemap Generation
- ✅ **Standalone Script**: `scripts/generate-sitemap.js` - generates SEO-optimized sitemaps
- ✅ **PM2 Automation**: Daily cron job (`0 4 * * *`) with fault tolerance
- ✅ **Quality Filtering**: Top 10K movies, 10K series, 3K persons by popularity
- ✅ **Tiered Priorities**: 1.0 for key hubs/blockbusters, 0.5-0.9 for regular content
- ✅ **SEO Metadata**: `lastmod`, `changefreq: daily`, proper priority distribution
- ✅ **Git Integration**: Sitemaps excluded from version control

### Commands
- `npm run generate-sitemap` - Generate sitemaps manually
- `pm2 start ecosystem.config.cjs` - Start PM2 processes including sitemap cron
- `curl https://themoviebrowser.com/` - Test no-JS rendering
